The 1961 red Burgundies are truly great, firm, well balanced and long-lived. The crop was a small one, the demand was great, and the price at the vineyard was inevitably expensive. The white Burgundies are fairly full-bodied, but have the racy breed of the 1952s. Our suggestion is to acquire them now, while still available, and at these relatively low prices.
